column2: Question
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Governor Brian Kemp?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Senator Davide Perdue?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of former gubernatorial candidate Stacey Abrams?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of former Governor Nathan Deal?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of President Donald Trump?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of the Affordable Care Act?
Do you have a favorable or unfavorable impression of Speaker of the House Nancy Pelosi?
How satisfied are you with the way things are going in Georgia today?
How satisfied are you with the way things are going in the U.S. today?
Georgia might replace its electronic voting machines with a paper ballot-based system. If so, which of the following would you prefer:
column3: Paper ballot that would be filled in by the voter
paper ballot that would be filled in by a computer

column2: The State of Georgia has a policy that says registered voters who don’t exercise their right to vote or contact election officials over several years will eventually be removed from the registration roll due to inactivity. Do you support this policy or not?
How likely is it that obstacles to voting or problems with voting machines affected the outcome of Georgia’s 2018 election for governor?
Should the Georgia Legislature increase, decrease, or leave unchanged the 21-day early in-person voting period?
Should the Georgia Legislature consider raising taxes on cigarettes and e-cigarette products to help pay for public health care funding?
Do you approve or disapprove of a proposal to tax phone lines, TV subscriptions and internet streaming services like Netflix to raise money for building internet lines in rural areas of Georgia?
Should Georgia expand eligibility for Medicaid, which provides health care to the poor?

The Trump Administration wants to allow states to require adults without disabilities to be working or looking for work in order to be eligible for Medicaid benefits. Would you support such a change in Georgia?
Should the Georgia Legislature allow gun owners to carry a concealed weapon without a permit?
Should the Georgia Legislature increase the age to purchase an assault weapon from 18 to 21?
Last year, a new state law went into effect that bans hand-held cell phone use while driving. Do you obey this law all of the time, most of the time, seldom, or never?
